 Banks of mist still crossed the blue of the mountains beyond the lake, but here and there a peak was tipped with ocher under the cloudless turquoise of the sky. Four tremendous trucks thundered by one after another. He went up to the rail of the balcony and wondered if he had ever satisfied the familiar whim by going platchâ€”had he? had he? You could never know, really. One floor below, and somewhat adjacently, stood Ada engrossed in the view.

